Step 2 — Download Character from Mixamo

Go to Mixamo website

Sign up / log in

Click Characters

Choose any character

Click: Use this Character


Step 3 — Download Animations

Search for animations.
- Walking
- Search: Walking
- Download: Without Skin

Search: Running
Download: Without Skin
Search: Breathing
Download: With Skin

Now you will have 3 files in Downloads.

Step 4 — Import Files into Unity

Copy downloaded files.

Paste into:

Unity Project → Assets Folder

Unity will import them automatically.

Step 5 — Add Character to Scene

In Assets folder

Drag the Breathing character into the Scene.

Resize if necessary using Scale Tool.

Step 6 — Export Textures

Select breathing character in Assets.

In Inspector:

Materials → Extract Textures

Unity opens a folder selection window.

Click:

Select Folder

Then:

Ignore

This extracts textures.

Step 7 — Export Materials

Still in Inspector:

Extract Materials

Again:

Select Folder
Ignore

Materials will now appear in project.

Step 8 — Create Animation Folder

In Assets:

Right Click → Create Folder

Name it:

Animation
Step 9 — Create Animation Clips

Select animation file (example breathing).

In Inspector:

Click the triangle icon next to animation

Click Edit

Scroll down.

Rename animation clip:

Breathing

Click outside to save.

Do the same for:

Running
Walking

Step 10 — Open Animator

Select the character in scene.

Open:

Window → Animation → Animator
Step 11 — Add Animations to Animator

Drag animation clips into the Animator window:

Running
Breathing
Walking

These appear as animation states.

Step 12 — Create Transitions

Connect animations.

Running → Breathing

Right click:

Running → Make Transition → Breathing
Breathing → Walking

Right click:

Breathing → Make Transition → Walking
Walking → Running

Right click:

Walking → Make Transition → Running

Now animations loop between each other.

Step 13 — Edit Transition Settings

Click transition arrow.

In Inspector:

Exit Time = 2

Apply the same setting to all transitions.

Step 14 — Enable Loop Animation

Select Breathing animation clip.

In Inspector:

Edit → Loop Time ✔

Do the same if needed for other animations.

Step 15 — Add Animator Component

Select the character in scene.

Add component:

Animator

In Animator Controller field:

Drag the animation controller you created.

Step 16 — Run the Scene

Press Play.

Character will:

Run
↓
Breath
↓
Walk
